snippet: A nurse tricked by Australian D.J.’s who called posing as Queen Elizabeth and Prince Charles to get information about Kate Middleton’s pregnancy was found dead on Friday.
abstract: British nurse Jacintha Saldanha is found dead from apparent suicide after mistakenly disclosing medical information about the pregnant Duchess of Cambridge to two Australian radio hosts who were playing a practical joke on air; hosts Mel Greig and Michael Christian impersonated Queen Elizabeth and Prince Charles in order to trick Saldanha, but it remains unclear why she took her own life.

byline.contributor: Matt Siegel contributed reporting from Sydney, Australia.

lead_paragraph: A nurse tricked by Australian D.J.’s who called posing as Queen Elizabeth and Prince Charles to get information about Kate Middleton’s pregnancy was found dead on Friday.

headline.seo: Nurse’s Death Stirs Sharp Criticism of Royal Prank Call
headline.main: Prank Call Seeking Royal Family Secrets Takes Horrifying Turn
